    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "2 Peter",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "Peter urges the Saints to make their calling and election sure\u2014Prophecy comes by the power of the Holy Ghost.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Simon Peter, a servant and an apostle of Jesus Christ, to them that have obtained like precious faith with us through the righteousness of God and our Saviour Jesus Christ:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 107:23.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0equally precious.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, the Standard of Righteousness.",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 135
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0of our God and Savior.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Grace and peace be multiplied unto you through the knowledge of God, and of Jesus our Lord,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:7 (5\u201310).",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "According as his divine power hath given unto us all things that pertain unto life and godliness, through the knowledge of him that hath called us to glory and virtue:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:55 (53\u201360).",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 45:8.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godliness.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0through, by.",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 149
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Virtue.",
                        "start": 160,
                        "end": 166
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whereby are given unto us exceeding great and precious promises: that by these ye might be partakers of the divine nature, having escaped the corruption that is in the world through lust.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Promise.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 93:28 (27\u201328).",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Purpose of.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 10:6.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 121
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Pet. 2:18.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 137
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 152
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lust.",
                        "start": 182,
                        "end": 186
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And beside this, giving all diligence, add to your faith virtue; and to virtue knowledge;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Diligence.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastity; Good Works; Virtue.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge; Learn; Study.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And to knowledge temperance; and to temperance patience; and to patience godliness;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0self-control. TG\u00a0Temperance.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Patience.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0reverence, piety, godliness.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And to godliness brotherly kindness; and to brotherly kindness charity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Benevolence; Kindness.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Charity.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For if these things be in you, and abound, they make you that ye shall neither be barren nor unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abundant Life.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0idle, unprofitable, injurious. TG\u00a0Barren.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 107:31 (30\u201331).",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But he that lacketh these things is blind, and cannot see afar off, and hath forgotten that he was purged from his old sins.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore the rather, brethren, give diligence to make your calling and election sure: for if ye do these things, ye shall never fall:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Election.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:44.",
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 133
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For so an entrance shall be ministered unto you abundantly into the everlasting kingdom of our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Immortality.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kingdom of God, on Earth.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore I will not be negligent to put you always in remembrance of these things, though ye know them, and be established in the present truth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, I think it meet, as long as I am in this tabernacle, to stir you up by putting you in remembrance;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0right, just, righteous.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 93:4, 35.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Knowing that shortly I must put off this my tabernacle, even as our Lord Jesus Christ hath shewed me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 21:19 (18\u201319).",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover I will endeavour that ye may be able after my decease to have these things always in remembrance.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1552
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For we have not followed cunningly devised fables, when we made known unto you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but were eyewitnesses of his majesty.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 1:4.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 17:2 (1\u20139); John 1:14. TG\u00a0Witness.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 147
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For he received from God the Father honour and glory, when there came such a voice to him from the excellent glory, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Witness of the Father.",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And this voice which came from heaven we heard, when we were with him in the holy mount.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Revelation; Witness of the Father.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 9:28 (28\u201336).",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We have also a more sure word of prophecy; whereunto ye do well that ye take heed, as unto a light that shineth in a dark place, until the day dawn, and the day star arise in your hearts:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a02\u00a0Pet. 1:19 We have therefore a more sure knowledge of the word of prophecy, to which word of prophecy ye do well that ye take heed\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 68:12; 88:3 (3\u20134); 132:19, 49.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 131:5.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 2:28; 22:16 (6\u201316).",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 165
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Knowing this first, that no prophecy of the scripture is of any private interpretation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a02\u00a0Pet. 1:20 \u2026 no prophecy of the scriptures is given of any private will of man.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prophecy.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Study of.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 40:8.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the prophecy came not in old time by the will of man: but holy men of God spake as they were moved by the Holy Ghost.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prophecy; Scriptures, Value of; Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Mission of.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Inspiration.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Gifts of.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}